ReactOS Shutdown Utility

Usage: shutdown [/?] [/i | /l | /s | /r | /g | /a | /p | /h | /e] [/f]
       [/m \\computer][/t xxx][/d [p|u:]xx:yy [/c "comment"]]

    No arguments or /?    Display this help.
    /i      Show the graphical user interface (GUI). This option must be the
            first one.
    /l      Log off on the local system only. Cannot be used with /m or /d.
    /s      Shutdown the computer.
    /r      Restart the computer.
    /g      Restart the computer and restart all the registered applications.
    /a      Cancel a delayed shutdown. Can only be used during the delay
            period.
    /p      Shutdown the local computer without any timeout or warning. Can be
            used with /d or /f.
    /h      Hibernate the local computer. Usable with /f.
    /e      Document the reason for the unexpected computer shutdown.
    /m \\computer  Specify the target computer (UNC/IP address).
    /t xxx  Set the timeout period to xxx seconds before shutting down.
            The valid range starts from 0 to 315360000 (10 years),
            30 being the default value.
    /c "comment"  Comment on the reason for shutdown or restart.
            512 characters maximum allowed.
    /f      Force running applications to close without warning users. If you
            do not specify any other parameter, this option will also log off.
    /d [p|u:]xx:yy  Give the reason code for the shutdown or the restart.
            p indicates that the shutdown or the restart is planned.
            u indicates that the reason is defined by the user.
            If neither p nor u are specified, the shutdown or the restart are
            not planned.
            xx is the major reason code (positive integer smaller than 256).
            yy is the minor reason code (positive integer smaller than 65536).
